		<div class="post-3245 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-art category-sita-sings-the-blues" id="post-3245">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/08/09/original-sita-sings-the-blues-paintings/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Original Sita Sings the Blues Paintings">Original Sita Sings the Blues Paintings</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>Someone has been emailing me saying they REALLY want to buy an original <em><a href="http://sitasingstheblues.com/">Sita Sings the Blues</a></em> painting. These have been in storage since I moved from New York to Urbana IL last year, but I just excavated them and took some crappy photos (reflective glass! Wide-angle pocket camera lens!) for her to choose from. Click thumbnail for hi-res jpeg.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SitaCaptive.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3246" title="SitaCaptive" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SitaCaptive-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/HanuRamSitaThrone.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3262" title="HanuRamSitaThrone" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/HanuRamSitaThrone-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Surphanaka.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3261" title="Surphanaka" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Surphanaka-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SitaGoddess.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3260" title="SitaGoddess" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SitaGoddess-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/GoldenDeer.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3259" title="GoldenDeer" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/GoldenDeer-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Rakshasa.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3258" title="Rakshasa" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Rakshasa-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Botanicals.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3257" title="Botanicals" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Botanicals-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mareecha.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3256" title="Mareecha" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mareecha-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Ayodhya.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3255" title="Ayodhya" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Ayodhya-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Hut.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3254" title="Hut" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Hut-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LuvOrKush.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3253" title="LuvOrKush" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LuvOrKush-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/RamHunts.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3252" title="RamHunts" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/RamHunts-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Ravana.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3251" title="Ravana" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Ravana-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LankaIsland.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3250" title="LankaIsland" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LankaIsland-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Valmiki.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3249" title="Valmiki" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Valmiki-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LakshmanRam.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3248" title="LakshmanRam" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LakshmanRam-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Hanuman.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-3247" title="Hanuman" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Hanuman-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></p>
<p>If anyone else wants to buy an original painting let me know: nina underscore paley at yahoo dot com. The outside dimensions of the wooden frames are about 12&#8243; x 14.8&#8243;. They&#8217;re about $1000 each, give or take for more or less complex/competent paintings.</p>
