<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/08/08/the-highest-praise/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to The Highest Praise">The Highest Praise</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>Some people love <a href="http://sitasingstheblues.com/"><em>Sita Sings the Blues</em></a> enough to devote time and energy (and probably money!) to protesting it in public. My movie is now in the same league as the paintings of the late <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M._F._Husain">M. F. Hussein</a>. I have arrived.<a href="http://forumforhinduawakening.org/dharma/news/2011/08/08/public-funds-used-to-denigrate-hinduism-protests-held-in-front-of-san-jose-museum-of-art/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3322" src="http://forumforhinduawakening.org/dharma/news/files/2011/08/More_Protest_with_placards_and_slogans.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" /></a></p>
<h2>Article: <a href="http://forumforhinduawakening.org/dharma/news/2011/08/08/public-funds-used-to-denigrate-hinduism-protests-held-in-front-of-san-jose-museum-of-art/">Troll Sena protests Sita Sings the Blues in San Jose</a></h2>
<p>Related: Aseem Chhabra on <em>Sita Sings the Blues</em> and free speech, in the <a href="http://www.mumbaimirror.com/article/54/2011080720110807052728135114f274a/Battling-for-free-speech.html"><em>Mumbai Mirror</em></a>.</p>
