		<div class="post-1955 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-art category-merch category-quilting category-sita-sings-the-blues" id="post-1955">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/04/25/laxmi-devi-quilt/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Laxmi Devi quilt">Laxmi Devi quilt</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>Here&#8217;s what I&#8217;ve been working on the past couple weeks:</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Laxmi-finished.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1956" title="Laxmi finished" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Laxmi-finished-424x640.jpg" alt="" width="424" height="640" /></a>Yep that&#8217;s &#8220;Laxmi&#8221; from <em><a href="http://sitasingstheblues.com/">Sita Sings the Blues</a></em>. Cotton fabric, polyester batting, polyester thread. 52&#8243; wide by 72&#8243; high &#8211; twice as big as any of my <a href="http://new-savanna.blogspot.com/2011/04/paleys-summa-quiltologica.html"><em>4 Elements</em></a> panels. I might sew some shiny gold sequin things coming out of Her open hand to symbolize the <a href="http://people.tribe.net/12d1a4aa-c412-4c79-9aa4-a1bff9ce2934/blog/09d31472-03ab-438a-adcd-3c967f9c1344">gold coins</a> that are often shown pouring out of it. <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/04/25/laxmi-devi-quilt/#more-1955" class="more-link">Continue reading Laxmi Devi quilt</a></p>
